content: I apologize for the mistake earlier. Joseph Miller, the son of William Mueller and Eliza Gardner, was a lawyer who practiced in Huntington, West Virginia. He served as the Prosecuting Attorney for Cabell County from 1877 to 1880 and was appointed United States Attorney for the Southern District of West Virginia by President Grover Cleveland in 1893. He also served as a delegate to the Democratic National Convention in 1908. He died in Huntington on February 22, 1921.
